      h2 Results
      p The table summarizes appraised values from various Texas CADs, ARBs, Arbitrators, SOAH Judge, and Courts, as a percentage of Historical Cost New (HCN). While none of these entities fully embraced the valuation model, they generally accepted or did not oppose its findings due to strong supporting evidence. Many Texas CADs accepted the Good Faith Estimate (GFE) of Market Value (MV) at around 50% of HCN. Over 90% of the cases resulted in accepted or near-GFE values. Some accounts remain pending with settlements expected.
